Description: Shoulder sherd (mended from two fragments) of East Greek Black Polychrome pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; pale orange fabric with large quantity of gold mica inclusions; exterior: parts of three incised tongues alternating black, added white, and black; below, traces of added white and red banding.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.257, no.7)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.54)
